Amazon Alexa Review Sentiment Analysis using Machine Learning

📌 Project Overview

Customer reviews provide valuable insights into user satisfaction and product performance. Automatically classifying reviews as positive or negative helps businesses monitor customer sentiment, improve products, and enhance user experience.

This project develops an NLP-based Sentiment Analysis system using the Amazon Alexa Reviews Dataset. It applies text preprocessing, feature engineering, and multiple machine learning algorithms to classify customer reviews as Positive or Negative. The project follows a complete machine learning pipeline—from exploratory data analysis and text preprocessing to model training, hyperparameter tuning, and evaluation.

🎯 Objectives
Analyze Amazon Alexa customer reviews.
Perform exploratory data analysis (EDA).
Preprocess textual data using NLP techniques.
Convert text into numerical features using Bag-of-Words.
Train and compare multiple machine learning models.
Optimize model performance using Grid Search and Cross Validation.
Predict customer sentiment from unseen reviews.

📊 Dataset
Dataset: Amazon Alexa Reviews Dataset
The dataset contains customer reviews of Amazon Alexa devices along with ratings and sentiment labels.

Features
Rating
Verified Reviews
Feedback (Target Variable)
Product Variation
Review Date

Target Variable

Feedback	Sentiment
0	Negative
1	Positive
