📈 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

The dataset was explored to understand customer review patterns before model development.

Data Exploration
Verified dataset dimensions
Checked data types
Confirmed there were no missing values
Created a review length feature
Statistical Analysis

Performed analysis on:

Rating distribution
Feedback distribution
Product variation analysis
Review length statistics
Data Visualization

Generated multiple visualizations including:

Rating Distribution Bar Chart
Feedback Distribution
Pie Charts
Review Length Histograms
Word Clouds
Product Variation Analysis
🔍 Key Insights
No missing values were found in the dataset.
Approximately 92% of reviews are positive, indicating a class imbalance.
Reviews with ratings of 1–2 are generally associated with negative feedback, while ratings of 3–5 correspond to positive feedback.
Product variations received different average ratings.
Word clouds highlighted commonly used positive and negative terms, providing qualitative insights into customer sentiment.

📝 Text Preprocessing
To prepare the review text for machine learning, the following NLP preprocessing steps were performed:
Removed special characters using Regular Expressions
Converted text to lowercase
Tokenized reviews into words
Removed stopwords using NLTK
Applied Porter Stemming
Built a cleaned text corpus

🔤 Feature Engineering
The cleaned text was transformed into numerical features using the Bag-of-Words approach.
Feature Extraction
CountVectorizer
Maximum vocabulary size: 2500 words
The resulting feature matrix was then scaled using MinMaxScaler before model training.

🤖 Machine Learning Models
Three supervised learning algorithms were implemented and compared.
1. Random Forest Classifier
Model Training
Prediction
Confusion Matrix
Cross Validation
Hyperparameter Optimization using GridSearchCV
2. XGBoost Classifier
Model Training
Prediction
Performance Evaluation
3. Decision Tree Classifier
Model Training
Prediction
Confusion Matrix

⚙️ Model Evaluation
The models were evaluated using:
Training Accuracy
Testing Accuracy
Accuracy Score
Confusion Matrix
K-Fold Cross Validation
GridSearchCV
Stratified K-Fold Validation

This allowed comparison of model performance and selection of the best-performing classifier.

