📌 Results
Successfully developed an end-to-end NLP pipeline for sentiment classification.
Applied text preprocessing techniques to convert raw customer reviews into machine learning-ready features.
Compared the performance of Random Forest, Decision Tree, and XGBoost classifiers.
Evaluated model performance using cross-validation, confusion matrices, and hyperparameter tuning.
Demonstrated how machine learning can be applied to automatically classify customer feedback for business intelligence and customer experience analysis.

📚 Future Improvements
Implement TF-IDF vectorization for richer text representation.
Experiment with Word2Vec, GloVe, or FastText embeddings.
Fine-tune transformer-based models such as BERT for higher classification accuracy.
Address class imbalance using techniques such as SMOTE or class weighting.
Deploy the model as a web application using Streamlit or Flask for real-time sentiment prediction.

